# Testing Rules — Velora Bundles

## Testing philosophy
- Unit tests for: Shopify Function logic, discount calculations, webhook handlers
- Integration tests for: loader/action functions, DB operations
- Manual QA: full user flows on dev store before every PR to main

## Unit test pattern (Vitest)
```typescript
// tests/discount.test.ts
import { describe, it, expect } from "vitest";
import { calculateDiscount } from "~/utils/discount";

describe("calculateDiscount", () => {
  it("applies percentage discount correctly", () => {
    const result = calculateDiscount({
      type: "PERCENTAGE",
      value: 10,
      originalPrice: 100
    });
    expect(result.finalPrice).toBe(90);
    expect(result.savedAmount).toBe(10);
  });

  it("applies fixed amount discount correctly", () => {
    const result = calculateDiscount({
      type: "FIXED_AMOUNT",
      value: 15,
      originalPrice: 100
    });
    expect(result.finalPrice).toBe(85);
  });

  it("never discounts below zero", () => {
    const result = calculateDiscount({
      type: "FIXED_AMOUNT",
      value: 200,
      originalPrice: 50
    });
    expect(result.finalPrice).toBeGreaterThanOrEqual(0);
  });
});
```

## Shopify Function test pattern
```typescript
// extensions/velora-discount/src/index.test.ts
import { describe, it, expect } from "vitest";
import { run } from "./index";

const createInput = (productIds: string[], qty: number) => ({
  cart: {
    lines: productIds.map((id, i) => ({
      id: `line_${i}`,
      quantity: qty,
      merchandise: { product: { id } }
    }))
  },
  shop: {
    metafield: {
      value: JSON.stringify([{
        productIds,
        minQuantity: 2,
        discountPercentage: 10
      }])
    }
  }
});

describe("Shopify Function", () => {
  it("applies discount when bundle matched", () => {
    const input = createInput(["prod_1", "prod_2"], 2);
    const result = run(input);
    expect(result.discounts).toHaveLength(1);
    expect(result.discounts[0].value.percentage.value).toBe("10");
  });

  it("no discount when quantity below minimum", () => {
    const input = createInput(["prod_1", "prod_2"], 1);
    const result = run(input);
    expect(result.discounts).toHaveLength(0);
  });
});
```

## Webhook HMAC verification test
```typescript
// tests/webhooks.test.ts
import { describe, it, expect } from "vitest";
import { verifyWebhookHmac } from "~/utils/webhooks.server";

describe("Webhook HMAC verification", () => {
  it("accepts valid HMAC", async () => {
    const body = JSON.stringify({ id: "order_123" });
    const secret = process.env.SHOPIFY_API_SECRET!;
    const validHmac = generateTestHmac(body, secret);
    
    const isValid = await verifyWebhookHmac(body, validHmac, secret);
    expect(isValid).toBe(true);
  });

  it("rejects invalid HMAC", async () => {
    const isValid = await verifyWebhookHmac(
      '{"id": "order_123"}',
      "invalid_hmac",
      process.env.SHOPIFY_API_SECRET!
    );
    expect(isValid).toBe(false);
  });
});
```

## Manual QA checklist — run before every PR to main

### Install + auth flow
- [ ] Fresh install on dev store via Partner Dashboard
- [ ] OAuth redirect completes successfully
- [ ] Onboarding wizard shows for new install
- [ ] App loads in Shopify Admin iframe
- [ ] Uninstall → shop.isActive = false in DB
- [ ] Reinstall → shop.isActive = true, existing data preserved

### Bundle CRUD
- [ ] Create fixed bundle with 2 products
- [ ] Create bundle with 3 volume discount tiers
- [ ] Live preview updates as fields change
- [ ] Save bundle → appears in list
- [ ] Edit bundle → changes saved correctly
- [ ] Archive bundle → disappears from active list
- [ ] Free plan: create 2nd bundle → upgrade prompt shows

### Storefront widget
- [ ] Widget appears on product page (Dawn theme)
- [ ] Widget appears on product page (at least 1 other theme)
- [ ] Radio options show correctly with pricing
- [ ] "Most Popular" badge shows on correct tier
- [ ] Strikethrough original price shows correctly
- [ ] Variant selectors appear for products with variants
- [ ] Mobile view: 375px — widget still readable
- [ ] Select bundle option → click ATC → correct items in cart
- [ ] Discount applied correctly at checkout

### Billing
- [ ] Free plan: 1 bundle limit enforced
- [ ] Upgrade to Starter $9.99 → plan updates in DB
- [ ] 14-day trial starts correctly
- [ ] Downgrade plan → plan updates in DB
- [ ] Settings page shows correct current plan

### Webhooks
```bash
# Test each webhook via CLI
shopify app webhook trigger --topic=orders/paid
shopify app webhook trigger --topic=app/uninstalled
shopify app webhook trigger --topic=customers/data_request
shopify app webhook trigger --topic=customers/redact
shopify app webhook trigger --topic=shop/redact
```
- [ ] orders/paid → bundle analytics incremented
- [ ] app/uninstalled → shop.isActive = false
- [ ] GDPR webhooks → respond 200 (no data to delete)
- [ ] Invalid HMAC → 401 response

### Analytics
- [ ] Dashboard shows correct MRR stat
- [ ] Widget views increment on page load
- [ ] Click-through rate calculates correctly
- [ ] Revenue chart renders (30 day view)
- [ ] Top bundle card shows correct bundle

### Performance
- [ ] Widget loads under 300ms (check DevTools Network tab)
- [ ] Admin pages load under 2s
- [ ] Lighthouse score > 80 on main pages
- [ ] Zero console errors in production mode

### Security
- [ ] Request shop A data while authenticated as shop B → 403
- [ ] Send webhook with invalid HMAC → 401
- [ ] SQL injection attempt via bundle name → no effect
- [ ] XSS attempt in bundle title → escaped in widget

## Edge cases — always test these
- Bundle with product that was deleted from Shopify → graceful error message
- Bundle with 0 discount value → validation error shown
- Store with 0 products → empty product picker with message
- Duplicate webhook (same shopifyWebhookId) → processed once only
- Very long product name (100+ chars) → truncated in widget
- Non-English store (Japanese, Arabic) → widget renders correctly
- Store currency is EUR/GBP → prices shown in correct currency
